#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:2
msgid "Cost Functions"
msgstr "Funciones de Coste"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:11
msgid ""
"The :mod:`qilisdk.cost_functions` module turns the raw outputs returned "
"by functionals into single scalar values that optimizers can minimize. "
"Each cost function inspects the "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` produced"
" by a backend and evaluates a problem-specific metric such as an "
"observable expectation value or the energy of an abstract optimization "
"model."
msgstr ""
"El módulo :mod:`qilisdk.cost_functions` convierte las salidas brutas "
"devueltas por los funcionales en valores escalares únicos que los "
"optimizadores pueden minimizar. Cada función de coste inspecciona el "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` producido "
"por un backend y evalúa una métrica específica del problema, como el valor "
"esperado de un observable o la energía de un modelo de optimización abstracto."

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:16
msgid "You will typically use cost functions to:"
msgstr "Normalmente se usan las funciones de coste para:"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:18
msgid ""
"score intermediate iterations inside a "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.variational_program.VariationalProgram`"
msgstr ""
"puntuar iteraciones intermedias dentro de un "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.variational_program.VariationalProgram`"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:19
msgid ""
"post-process "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` samples "
"into meaningful costs"
msgstr ""
"postprocesar muestras de "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` en costes "
"significativos"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:20
msgid ""
"translate "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` states "
"into expectation values"
msgstr ""
"traducir estados de "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` en valores "
"esperados"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:24
msgid "CostFunction Interface"
msgstr "Interfaz de CostFunction"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:26
msgid ""
"The abstract :class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction` "
"base class exposes a single public method, "
":meth:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction.compute_cost`. "
"It dispatches on the concrete type of the functional result and calls the"
" appropriate protected hook:"
msgstr ""
"La clase base abstracta "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction` expone un único "
"método público, "
":meth:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction.compute_cost`. "
"Despacha según el tipo concreto del resultado funcional y llama al gancho "
"protegido apropiado:"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:30
msgid ""
"It dispatches on the content of the "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult`, "
"inspecting the available readout results (samples, expectation values, "
"final state) to compute the cost."
msgstr ""
"Despacha según el contenido del "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult`, "
"inspeccionando los resultados de lectura disponibles (muestras, valores "
"esperados, estado final) para calcular el coste."

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:33
msgid ""
"If your workflow introduces new functional result types you can subclass "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction` and register "
"additional handlers in ``self._handlers`` or override the protected "
"methods above. Custom implementations must return a real or complex "
"number that represents the score you want to optimize."
msgstr ""
"Si su flujo de trabajo introduce nuevos tipos de resultado funcional, puede "
"crear una subclase de "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction` y registrar "
"manejadores adicionales en ``self._handlers`` o sobreescribir los métodos "
"protegidos anteriores. Las implementaciones personalizadas deben devolver un "
"número real o complejo que represente la puntuación a optimizar."

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:39
msgid "ObservableCostFunction"
msgstr "ObservableCostFunction"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:41
msgid ""
"The "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.observable_cost_function.ObservableCostFunction`"
" evaluates the expectation value of an observable against either a final "
"state (from time evolution) or the probability distribution of sampled "
"bitstrings. It accepts three interchangeable representations for the "
"observable: a :class:`~qilisdk.core.qtensor.QTensor`, a symbolic "
":class:`~qilisdk.analog.hamiltonian.Hamiltonian`, or a single "
":class:`~qilisdk.analog.hamiltonian.PauliOperator`. Internally, all "
"inputs are converted to :class:`~qilisdk.core.qtensor.QTensor` so the "
"same numeric pipeline can be reused for both analog and digital results."
msgstr ""
"La "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.observable_cost_function.ObservableCostFunction` "
"evalúa el valor esperado de un observable frente a un estado final (de la "
"evolución temporal) o la distribución de probabilidad de cadenas de bits "
"muestreadas. Acepta tres representaciones intercambiables para el observable: "
"un :class:`~qilisdk.core.qtensor.QTensor`, un "
":class:`~qilisdk.analog.hamiltonian.Hamiltonian` simbólico, o un único "
":class:`~qilisdk.analog.hamiltonian.PauliOperator`. Internamente, todas las "
"entradas se convierten a :class:`~qilisdk.core.qtensor.QTensor` para que la "
"misma cadena numérica pueda reutilizarse tanto para resultados analógicos "
"como digitales."

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:50
msgid "Example: expectation value from analog evolution"
msgstr "Ejemplo: valor esperado desde evolución analógica"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:95
msgid ""
"For sampling workflows, the cost function iterates through the "
"probability distribution exposed by "
":attr:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult.probabilities`"
" and accumulates the expectation value in the computational basis."
msgstr ""
"Para flujos de trabajo de muestreo, la función de coste itera sobre la "
"distribución de probabilidad expuesta por "
":attr:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult.probabilities` "
"y acumula el valor esperado en la base computacional."

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:101
msgid "ModelCostFunction"
msgstr "ModelCostFunction"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:103
msgid ""
"The "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.model_cost_function.ModelCostFunction` "
"bridges classical optimization models with quantum result objects. It "
"accepts any :class:`~qilisdk.core.model.Model` (including convenience "
"subclasses such as :class:`~qilisdk.core.model.QUBO`) and evaluates it "
"against measured bitstrings or the amplitudes of a final quantum state."
msgstr ""
"La "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.model_cost_function.ModelCostFunction` "
"conecta modelos de optimización clásica con objetos de resultado cuántico. "
"Acepta cualquier :class:`~qilisdk.core.model.Model` (incluyendo subclases "
"de conveniencia como :class:`~qilisdk.core.model.QUBO`) y lo evalúa frente "
"a cadenas de bits medidas o las amplitudes de un estado cuántico final."

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:108
msgid ""
"When the provided model is a :class:`~qilisdk.core.model.QUBO`, the cost "
"function automatically converts it into a Hamiltonian and computes the "
"expectation value. Otherwise, it maps each sample to the model's "
"variables, feeds them through :meth:`~qilisdk.core.model.Model.evaluate`,"
" and aggregates the resulting objective and constraint values."
msgstr ""
"Cuando el modelo proporcionado es un :class:`~qilisdk.core.model.QUBO`, la "
"función de coste lo convierte automáticamente en un Hamiltoniano y calcula "
"el valor esperado. De lo contrario, mapea cada muestra a las variables del "
"modelo, las procesa mediante "
":meth:`~qilisdk.core.model.Model.evaluate` y agrega los valores de objetivo "
"y restricción resultantes."

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:113
msgid "Example: scoring samples from a variational circuit"
msgstr "Ejemplo: puntuación de muestras de un circuito variacional"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:151
msgid "Cost Functions in Variational Programs"
msgstr "Funciones de Coste en Programas Variacionales"

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:153
msgid ""
"Variational workflows combine a parameterized "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional.Functional`, a classical "
"optimizer, and a "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction`. At each "
"optimizer iteration the backend executes the functional, obtains a "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult` object, "
"and feeds it into the configured cost function to obtain the scalar that "
"drives the optimization loop."
msgstr ""
"Los flujos de trabajo variacionales combinan un "
":class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional.Functional` parametrizado, un "
"optimizador clásico y una "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.cost_function.CostFunction`. En cada "
"iteración del optimizador, el backend ejecuta el funcional, obtiene un "
"objeto :class:`~qilisdk.functionals.functional_result.FunctionalResult`, y "
"lo alimenta a la función de coste configurada para obtener el escalar que "
"impulsa el bucle de optimización."

#: ../../modules/cost_functions/cost_functions.rst:188
msgid ""
"Swapping the cost function lets you explore alternative objective "
"definitions without touching the functional itself. For example, you can "
"start with "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.observable_cost_function.ObservableCostFunction`"
" to reproduce a physics-inspired energy expectation and later try "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.model_cost_function.ModelCostFunction` to"
" include constraint penalties from a combinatorial problem."
msgstr ""
"Intercambiar la función de coste permite explorar definiciones de objetivo "
"alternativas sin modificar el funcional en sí. Por ejemplo, se puede "
"comenzar con "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.observable_cost_function.ObservableCostFunction` "
"para reproducir una expectativa de energía inspirada en física y luego "
"probar "
":class:`~qilisdk.cost_functions.model_cost_function.ModelCostFunction` para "
"incluir penalizaciones por restricciones de un problema combinatorio."
